results.occurrenceRemarks: Once extirpated, white rhinos were re-introduced to northern Botswana (Chief's Island in the Okavango Delta) in 2002 from South Africa.  (It was a sort of wildlife trade: South Africa received roan antelope in exchange for 20 white rhinos.)  These particular two rhino escaped their island confines.  I encountered them at night a couple days before this observation.  We reported their presence and a military escort was sent out to 'shepherd' the rhinos.
